<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1113,1245]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Diagnosis of subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahl, 1966" authorityName="Dahl" authorityYear="1966" box="[418,592,1113,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Trichoceridae" genus="Metatrichocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[418,592,1113,1137]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Metatrichocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains an object of discussions, but following 
<bibRefCitation author="Krzeminska" box="[1154,1388,1113,1137]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" refString="Krzeminska, E. (2002 a) A new subgenus and two new species of the genus Trichocera Meigen, 1803 (Diptera: Trichoceridae). Annales zoologici, 52 (2), 201 - 205." type="journal article" year="2002" yearSuffix="a">
Krzemińska (
<number box="[1306,1367,1113,1137]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2002.0">2002</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
, the main features are balloon like gonocoxites; gonostyles distinctly different from gonocoxites and adorned with armature; parameres in most species thin, especially in distal portion, lateral apodemes strongly elongated and narrow, more than three times longer than wide.
</paragraph>
